# Mobile-first / PWA Rules

Houston is used by field teams on phones first.

## Mobile-first UI
- Build mobile layout first; enhance with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`.
- No desktop-first layout later patched for mobile.
- No horizontal page scroll.
- No hover-only or desktop-only interaction.
- Critical actions must be reachable on mobile.
- Prefer sticky bottom primary actions for field workflows.
- Keep tap targets comfortable and spaced.

## PWA constraints
- Preserve manifest/installability basics.
- Preserve explicit offline/network failure states.
- Do not cache authenticated operational API data casually.
- Do not make stale operational data look fresh.
- Do not add push, background sync, or aggressive service-worker caching without approval.

## Forms
- Phone keyboard friendly inputs.
- Visible labels or accessible names.
- Inline validation near the field.
- Pending submit state prevents double-submit.

## Performance/accessibility
- Avoid heavy dependencies and unnecessary animations.
- Respect reduced motion.
- Icon-only buttons need accessible names.
- Loading/empty/error/offline states are mandatory.

## Tests
When changing mobile/PWA behavior, cover route, nav, sticky action, form state, offline/error state, or query invalidation.